channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Colorado Primary: Lauren Boebert Pulls Out a Win to Take Over Retired Rep. Ken Buck's Seat
Popular Republican and Trump running mate contender makes first Senate endorsement in 2024 races
item.description: Republican Sen. Tim Scott of South Carolina, who's under consideration as former President Donald Trump's running mate, endorses former Rep. Mike Rogers in battleground Michigan's GOP Senate primary

item.title: Some Intel Officials Who Dissed Hunter Laptop Story on CIA Payroll
item.description: Some of the 51 intelligence officials who signed on to a letter in the final weeks of the 2020 presidential campaign that the New York Post's story about Hunter Biden's laptop had "all the classic earmarks of a Russian information operation" were on the CIA's payroll.

item.title: NYT Siccing an Astonishing 29 Fact Checkers on Trump-Biden Debateâ€”but Make It Clear Who They're After
Biden debate prep focused on ways to 'trigger' Trump as former president relies on campaigning: reports
item.description: President Biden's debate prep is focusing on ways he can "trigger" former President Trump during the first presidential debate, while the latter is leaning on his campaign experience.

item.title: Rep. John Curtis Wins Utah GOP Primary for Romney's Open Seat
item.description: Rep. John Curtis has won the Utah GOP primary for Mitt Romney's open U.S. Senate seat, defeating one opponent who was endorsed by former President Donald Trump and others who said they supported Trump's agenda.

item.title: NY16 Primary: Hamas Caucus Member Jamaal Bowman Goes Down in Defeat As Democrats Choose Latimer
Black GOP lawmakers hold 'Congress, Cognac, and Cigars' event in key swing state
item.description: Rep. Wesley Hunt spoke with Fox News Digital about his and Rep. Byron Donalds' efforts to turn the Black vote out for former President Trump.

item.title: Biggs Wins GOP Nod for House in S.C, Over Trump-backed Candidate
item.description: Sheri Biggs, a nurse practitioner and Air National Guard officer, won the Republican nomination for the U.S. House in South Carolina's 3rd District on Tuesday, defeating a challenger who called himself former President Donald Trump's pastor. In November, Biggs will be a ...

item.title: Could a Michigan Senate Seat Be in Play This November?
The veepstakes goes 'Apprentice': Will Trump really pick Rubio, Vance or Burgum?
item.description: The final leg of former President Trump's veepstakes is underway, and only three contenders live to tell the tale. Here's what to look out for from each of them.

item.title: Stephen Moore to Newsmax: Trump Should Invoke Reagan in Debate
item.description: Stephen Moore, a senior economic adviser under former President Donald Trump, said the Republican presumptive nominee should invoke Ronald Reagan's famous line during his upcoming debate, because the answer is no less true today than it was in 1980.

item.title: Mike Pence Gets Ratio'd After Controversial Statement About Julian Assange Being Set Free
Mike Kennedy advances past crowded GOP primary to secure nomination for open Utah House seat
item.description: Republican voters on Tuesday picked who they wanted to represent them in the upcoming general election race for Utah's open 3rd Congressional District seat.

item.title: Rep. Boebert Wins GOP Primary in Colorado's 4th District
item.description: Rep. Lauren Boebert won Tuesday's Republican primary in Colorado in a race that she jumped into last year.
